Parents often do not recognise depression in teenagers as the symptoms differ from that of adults. This leaves many young people suffering in silence. Depression is a medical illness that can interfere with your ability to handle daily activities which affect sleeping, eating and managing your school work. It can affect all teens regardless of their gender, popularity, academic success or social activities. Observable changes: How to help: To make the world a better place for children, do not point fingers at the visible mistakes but start by being the change you want to see!